Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.98,0:01:34.51,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"Loss"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.35,0:01:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're reassigning me as an instructor?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.94,0:01:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.39,0:01:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have two weeks to prepare.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.78,0:01:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will undergo special training
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.89,0:01:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before taking your post in\NGurantseere Cosmopolitan Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.82,0:01:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were an exceptional pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.20,0:01:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the optimum post\Nfor making the most of those skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.08,0:02:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The MJP Project was founded in GC 35\Nto develop humans suited for space life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.54,0:02:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the Wulgaru invasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.31,0:02:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was decided that those over\Nthe age of 12 were to become pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.63,0:02:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were transferred to\NGurantseere Cosmopolitan Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:14.11,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,Open\NSPIRITS
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.76,0:02:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.47,0:02:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the sort of \Nthing you celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.08,0:02:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you say that?\NAren't you embarking on a new journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.87,0:02:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My job is to train children \Nwho were genetically
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.97,0:02:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Naltered before birth to fight on the frontline!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.48,0:02:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's depressing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.21,0:02:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those children were temporarily left\Nin the care of foster parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.70,0:02:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but we're going to erase \Nall of their personal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nmemories before they start school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.17,0:02:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if that's so they won't regret\Nleaving their old lives behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.38,0:02:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dealing with kids that lack both\Na past and future...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.42,0:02:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I can take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.47,0:02:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! Gimme another \Nmedium-sized beer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.84,0:02:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you even listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, screw that.\NGimme a bottle of premium saké!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.46,0:02:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't that why they \Nchose you, Rin-Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.39,0:03:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True, my piloting and \Nfighting days are over...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.70,0:03:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only job left for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.06,0:03:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But didn't you make it back alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.61,0:03:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the only survivor\Nwhen your unit got destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.73,0:03:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you pass on \Nthose survival skills?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.03,0:03:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.10,0:03:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.52,0:03:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to the Ioness Theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.15,0:03:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was a substantial \Nboost in engine efficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.03,0:03:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the human reaction time\Nfor those piloting the-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.32,0:03:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing in \Nthe middle of class?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.20,0:03:56.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, well, you see...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:03:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.91,0:03:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, umm, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.20,0:04:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-sorry, I didn't mean it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, my bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.82,0:04:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poopy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.46,0:04:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.34,0:04:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your bodyline is like that \Nof a beautiful Steyr.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.55,0:04:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've shot my heart with your\N hot loaded armor-piercing bullets,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.30,0:04:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,knocking me down!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.14,0:04:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are the students?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.14,0:04:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. On average,\Nthey are brimming with potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.35,0:04:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They follow their orders
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.16,0:04:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and have fast response times \Nin mock space battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.78,0:04:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is one team\Nthat is highly problematic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.45,0:04:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.57,0:04:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.99,0:04:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The team is composed \Nof students who were
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.96,0:04:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,originally unsuited for teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.89,0:04:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With impressive latent abilities,\Nthey definitely possess hidden potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.46,0:04:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they are lacking \Non the mental front.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.88,0:04:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are ill oriented for group work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.67,0:04:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.23,0:04:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will be their downfall as pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.18,0:04:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the flip side?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.89,0:05:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inversely, they could \Nbecome mentally strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.64,0:05:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once they master teamwork,\Nthey will outstrip the other teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.19,0:05:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, on what grounds...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.69,0:05:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have abnormally strong \Nsurvival instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.95,0:05:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes them ideal pilots
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.44,0:05:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for AHSMB units equipped \Nwith the JURIA-SYSTEM.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.28,0:05:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Train them! That is your mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.08,0:05:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.17,0:05:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.01,0:05:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rose 3's first and second thrusters\Nhave taken damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.05,0:05:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Power is down by 40%!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.76,0:05:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy fighters are \Napproaching from β34.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.39,0:05:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-they got me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.38,0:05:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?! What should I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.27,0:05:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kei, can't we help her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.81,0:05:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kei? Kei!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.28,0:05:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down. Think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.28,0:05:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should be able to save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.49,0:06:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm a hero, fight! Fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.34,0:06:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight so we can survive!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.08,0:06:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Harmonic values, increasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.58,0:06:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One through three are increasing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.62,0:06:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My armguards?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.58,0:06:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Red 5 removed its armguards,\NI could use them as shields...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.58,0:06:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Red 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.93,0:06:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! You're going \Nto become a hero with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.18,0:06:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Send a multi-launcher, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.20,0:06:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.65,0:06:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Tamaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.45,0:06:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about me! Everyone, \Nget out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a grip, Tamaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.23,0:06:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But at this rate, they'll take you and\Neveryone else down with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to make it back alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.05,0:06:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.76,0:07:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted to go on a date!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.21,0:07:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we make it back, \Nthat may not happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.44,0:07:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that serious answer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.89,0:07:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what you say \Nat a time like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.68,0:07:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell her she'll find a date!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.37,0:07:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.06,0:07:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue 1, take the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.23,0:07:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4, take the left. \NPurple 2, issue orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.03,0:07:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.50,0:07:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue 1, strike Unit 4 in the upper right\Nportion of Formation A.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.74,0:07:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4, fire at the bottom left\Nportion of Formation B.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.62,0:07:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep them in check and\Ncarve open a path for Rose 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.11,0:07:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ally units have taken 32.6% damage.\NAmmo down to 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.26,0:07:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can only fight for \Nanother 12 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probability of return: -15%.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.84,0:07:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't possibly continue to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.05,0:07:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vice Chief of Staff, please issue\Nthe order for them to retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.52,0:07:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.31,0:07:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retreat is not an option!\NDon't run! Fight the beasts!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.98,0:07:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't! At this rate,\Nwe're going to lose all of the units.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.86,0:08:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.15,0:08:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you realize how much money\Nwe've put into them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.16,0:08:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue 1, Gold 4, Red 5, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.09,0:08:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.04,0:08:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-don't turn and run!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.51,0:08:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm having control issues here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.31,0:08:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vice Chief of Staff, please \Norder them to retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.84,0:08:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All units, retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.68,0:08:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Force Rose 3 to purge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.77,0:08:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.96,0:08:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2, forcibly purge \NRose 3. Copy that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.23,0:08:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.83,0:08:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm light!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.95,0:08:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rose 3, retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.24,0:08:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.82,0:08:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we use Rose 3's \Nboosters as missiles...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.42,0:08:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They should pack a real wallop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.50,0:09:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue 1, protect Rose 3 as you retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4, serve as backup \Nwhile you retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.01,0:09:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5, slow withdrawal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.20,0:09:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's everyone doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.93,0:09:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll reach the ship in just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.47,0:09:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kei, you should head back as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.76,0:09:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.90,0:09:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.41,0:09:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.33,0:09:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.70,0:09:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5's transmission has been damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.04,0:09:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Primary reactor has ceased functioning.\NEnergy reserves down by 25%.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.62,0:09:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Auxiliary power is dropping fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.29,0:09:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Auxiliary thrusters are totally shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.04,0:09:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't change its course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The emergency escape unit is out, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.53,0:09:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to cut our \Nlosses with the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.35,0:09:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha-?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.01,0:09:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't the least bit okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.90,0:09:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine, so get back, Kei!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.18,0:09:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.06,0:09:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.06,0:10:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2, come back immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Izuru-!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll head on back after you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.09,0:10:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you say that?!\N You can't even move!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.74,0:10:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2, did you hear me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hero always makes \Nit back in one piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.66,0:10:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't die in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.37,0:10:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still want to draw manga and\Neat more of your insanely sweet cakes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.83,0:10:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.00,0:10:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.13,0:10:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.25,0:10:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AHSMB units...? Allies?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.52,0:10:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is...Team Doberman!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.69,0:10:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who gave them orders to sortie?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.48,0:10:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.40,0:10:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Team Doberman will hereby retrieve\NRed 5 and withdraw.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.36,0:10:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.70,0:10:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there was another able team,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.54,0:10:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should have included them\Nin the battle to begin with!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.20,0:11:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare he hold out on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.17,0:11:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.09,0:11:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2 has returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.72,0:11:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.56,0:11:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should I get a stretcher?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.89,0:11:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Better, just in case!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.77,0:11:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.31,0:11:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.52,0:11:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Wulgaru army has \Nstarted to pull back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.07,0:11:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe they are \Nheaded toward Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.87,0:11:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.00,0:11:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Care for a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.45,0:11:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.43,0:11:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made it back...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.13,0:11:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should have...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.34,0:11:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should have gotten out of there\Nwith the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.06,0:11:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.89,0:12:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to handle \Neverything by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.05,0:12:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you realize what would have\Nhappened if help hadn't come?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.69,0:12:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.06,0:12:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, everyone is giving \Nme a piece of their mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.40,0:12:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.40,0:12:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nothing to be happy about!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.29,0:12:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remove everything from \NBlock 3 to Block 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.37,0:12:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Send Rose 3 and Red 5 to Maintenance D.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.93,0:12:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.96,0:12:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh. We're administering \Nemergency repairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.43,0:12:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nbut they need a full overhaul in HQ's dock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.43,0:12:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That goes double for Rose 3 and Red 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.76,0:12:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rose 3 currently uses \Na navigational shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.10,0:12:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need to give it \Na maximum-power shield
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.22,0:12:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nthat can withstand enemy beams,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.44,0:12:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just like the ones Blue 1 and Red 5 use.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.56,0:12:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really! This is no time for sweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.73,0:12:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for super-premium dry saké!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.61,0:12:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.87,0:12:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the Vice Chief of Staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.92,0:12:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resting in his personal room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.33,0:13:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, GDF high command has requested
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.49,0:13:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we send them a copy of our \Nbattle report in all due haste.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.92,0:13:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You write it! I'll check \Nover it once it's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.54,0:13:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send over the battle logs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.58,0:13:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.81,0:13:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how long this war \Nis going to drag out...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.02,0:13:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who can say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.02,0:13:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even know what
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.30,0:13:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Wulgaru are after \Nor where they came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.31,0:13:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.73,0:13:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to have\Ninterrupted your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.82,0:13:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.83,0:13:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,February 4, 86 GC.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.84,0:13:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our units engaged what \Nwe believe to be an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Narmed Wulgaru recon force near FRB-1011.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.21,0:14:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We've been left in\Nthe dark, ever since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.93,0:14:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They came out of nowhere, striking\NEarth's frontier development base.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.68,0:14:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The armies stationed around the outer planets\Nwere dispatched immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.48,0:14:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus began Earth's first \Nwar in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.57,0:14:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We believe the Wulgaru armada is\Ncomposed of 1 massive mother ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.12,0:14:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5 large carriers, 800 space-faring vessels\Nand 3,000 mobile fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.81,0:14:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our combined global forces\Ninclude 15 million soldiers,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.79,0:14:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3,500 space-faring vessels and\N20,000 mobile fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.25,0:14:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite vastly superior numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.88,0:14:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,our results in battle have been dismal\Nas we gradually pull back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.42,0:14:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, even the most \Nfavorable calculations
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.92,0:14:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nshow them reaching Earth in...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.22,0:14:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this stuff awesome?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.27,0:14:48.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has a rich fragrance \Nand a refreshing zing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.73,0:14:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention the delicious fruity taste\Nthat explodes in your mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.77,0:14:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.29,0:14:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.10,0:14:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, you're putting perfectly\Ngood saké to waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.90,0:15:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y'know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.41,0:15:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So like, what do you think's \Ngonna happen to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.04,0:15:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this battle, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.79,0:15:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rin-Rin!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.21,0:15:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much we outnumber them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Ntheir technology is far superior to our own...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.63,0:15:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be the case, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we sent a bunch \Nof men after them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.77,0:15:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they can easily counter the attack\Nwith a handful of cutting-edge units.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.23,0:15:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.23,0:15:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They swoop in and then \Nswoop right back out,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.00,0:15:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they've suffered \Nsurprisingly few losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.51,0:15:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too many peanuts overwhelm\Nthe persimmon seeds!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.83,0:15:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't about persimmon seeds!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.66,0:15:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.03,0:15:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Don't take that attitude with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.01,0:15:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, I almost gave up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.42,0:15:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I almost gave up on Red 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.46,0:15:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rin-Rin!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.63,0:16:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not... supposed to give up\Non my own students!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.72,0:16:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not supposed to lose hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.43,0:16:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.62,0:16:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, you're a crying drunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.69,0:16:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki, go to your room \Nif you're gonna sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.37,0:16:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I'm staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.03,0:16:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More antacids?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.72,0:16:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it only natural to get an upset stomach\Nafter a battle like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.24,0:16:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed you guys don't have ulcers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.70,0:16:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a matter of time before\Nyou form a hole in your gut.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.49,0:16:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.42,0:16:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be nice if there was something\Nwe could do to help relax...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.46,0:16:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's crashing in three, two, one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.16,0:16:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.97,0:16:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huggie!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.31,0:16:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tamaki?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.20,0:16:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's just like a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.12,0:16:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, I have dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.11,0:16:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.52,0:17:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dream that I'm a baby and\Nsomeone is holding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.03,0:17:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I close my eyes,\Nsomeone gently pats me on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's just a dream, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.63,0:17:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but I'm sure someone cared\Nfor me like that once.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.29,0:17:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.88,0:17:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, didn't you think we were\Ngoing to die back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.51,0:17:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.66,0:17:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I die, do you think \Nthey'll inform the people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who used to pat my back?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.52,0:17:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's doubtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.48,0:17:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dang, you're cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.40,0:17:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gosh darn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.65,0:17:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naïve dudes like you are insensitive \Nto another's naïve beliefs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.70,0:17:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.53,0:17:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.74,0:17:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Let's head back to our own rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.41,0:17:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do something about Tamaki before you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.96,0:17:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Leader. Carry the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.06,0:18:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's drawing again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.74,0:18:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's like a tranquilizer for Izuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.59,0:18:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Izuru tried to protect \NTamaki, all on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.95,0:18:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.16,0:18:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.55,0:18:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.97,0:18:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly it is called \Na "picture book".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.75,0:18:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pictures are drawn to match the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.55,0:18:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot comprehend such books.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.01,0:18:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could anything save the truth\Nhold any value?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.92,0:18:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not understand, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.06,0:18:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they may be unable
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.69,0:19:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to understand us just as \Nwe fail to understand them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.73,0:19:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Auron Taul has spoken! Open the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.53,0:19:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is fighting the only option for those\Nwho cannot understand one another?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.80,0:19:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Team Rabbits will hereby return to\NGurantseere Cosmopolitan Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.89,0:19:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.10,0:19:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're taking the AHSMB units back to HQ,\Nwhere we'll fix them right up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.02,0:19:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take me with you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.40,0:19:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.65,0:19:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look after Rin-Rin for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.57,0:19:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm just fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.24,0:20:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just had a wee bit too much to drink.\NRight, Rin-Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.04,0:20:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that in front of my students!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.13,0:20:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna call you Rin-Rin!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.16,0:20:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.96,0:20:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you call her Rin-Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.55,0:20:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.88,0:20:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reika!\NWe're childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.42,0:20:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been calling her that since\Nelementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.83,0:20:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We went to different schools after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.13,0:20:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but then we met up again at\Nthe military academy, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.18,0:20:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Childhood friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.47,0:20:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like that backstory!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.31,0:20:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a manga!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.31,0:20:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what it must be like\Nto have a childhood friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.29,0:20:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit going on about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.49,0:20:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll reach the ground momentarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.62,0:20:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rin-Rin, see ya later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.62,0:20:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, quit calling me that!\NRin-Rin, see ya later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.12,0:20:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the head mechanic going?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't she going to GDF's headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.16,0:20:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she's dropping \Nby her home in Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.74,0:20:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her family is always \Ngiving her a hard time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.67,0:20:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe it or not, she's a rich heiress.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.76,0:20:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An heiress?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.01,0:20:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Saionji Pharmaceutical.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.64,0:20:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sponsor...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.86,0:21:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she became our head mechanic...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.72,0:21:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Against her parents' wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.60,0:21:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They disapproved? How dramatic!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.10,0:21:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your lives are just beginning, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.23,0:21:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a lot to look forward to,\Nnot just fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.19,0:21:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Survive this war! That's a must!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.57,0:21:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.69,0:21:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.67,0:21:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But dang does my head hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.71,0:21:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's drunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.47,0:21:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't introduced them yet, have I?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.75,0:21:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is Team Doberman.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.73,0:21:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are the team that rescued you\Nin that last battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.19,0:21:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're your seniors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.02,0:21:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are second gen MJP students\Nentering their third term.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.69,0:21:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Simon kept them a secret\Nwhile they were on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.11,0:22:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The team is composed of\NChandra, Randy and Patrick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.01,0:23:56.02,Copy of Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"Operation: Infiltrate a Planetoid Base"
